There have been seven arrests so far linked to the quarter of a billion rand 2014 asbestos roofing project in the Free State. On Thursday afternoon the seventh suspect handed himself over in Richards Bay. All seven will appear in court in Bloemfontein on Friday.  Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Seven people linked to the controversial Free State Asbestos Project will appear in court on Friday. The last suspect handed himself over to the police on Thursday. READ: SACP wants changes to tender procurement regulations The South African Communist Party has welcomed the arrests. The party believes it marks the beginning of an era of accountability but it still feels the tender system should be rolled back as it's flawed. The organisation also said arrests must be followed by successful prosecutions, severe prison sentences, and asset seizures.